catgirl is a lightweight IRC client for the terminal written by
June McEnroe.

It provides tab completion, nickname coloring, URL detection,
message filtering, chat logging, and TLS support through libtls.

catgirl follows a simple Unix philosophy and intentionally avoids
features such as built-in multi-network support, automatic
reconnection, and dynamic configuration.

Multiple networks can be handled by running multiple instances in
tmux(1), screen(1), or separate terminal windows.

Homepage:
https://git.causal.agency/catgirl
